Given the ellipse $C$: $\dfrac{x^{2}}{a^{2}} + \dfrac{y^{2}}{b^{2}} = 1 (a > b > 0)$ passes through the point $(0,1)$, and its eccentricity is $\dfrac{\sqrt{2}}{2}$.

(Ⅰ) Find the equation of the ellipse $C$;  
(Ⅱ) Let $O$ be the origin, and the ellipse $C$ intersects with the line $y=kx+1$ at two distinct points $A$ and $B$. Find the maximum area of $\triangle OAB$.

In this square array of 25 dots arranged in a 5x5 grid, four dots are to be chosen at random. What is the probability that the four dots will be collinear? Express your answer as a common fraction.

[asy]
size(75);
for(int i = 0; i<5; ++i)
for(int j = 0; j<5; ++j)
dot((i,j),linewidth(7));
[/asy]

14. (13 points) Let the quadratic equation in $x$, $2 x^{2}-t x-2=0$, have two roots $\alpha, \beta(\alpha<\beta)$.
(1) If $x_{1} 、 x_{2}$ are two different points in the interval $[\alpha, \beta]$, prove that $4 x_{1} x_{2}-t\left(x_{1}+x_{2}\right)-4<0$;
(2) Let $f(x)=\frac{4 x-t}{x^{2}+1}$, and the maximum and minimum values of $f(x)$ on the interval $[\alpha, \beta]$ be $f_{\max }$ and $f_{\min }$, respectively. Let $g(t)=f_{\max }-f_{\min }$. Find the minimum value of $g(t)$.

Given that a hyperbola and an ellipse $\frac{x^{2}}{36}+ \frac{y^{2}}{27}=1$ have the same foci, and the length of the conjugate axis of the hyperbola is $4$.
(I) Find the equation of the hyperbola;
(II) Find the equations of the asymptotes of the hyperbola.

14. Let $\left\{a_{n}\right\}$ be a sequence of positive numbers, with the sum of its first $n$ terms being $S_{n}$, and for all natural numbers $n$, we have
$$
S_{n}=\frac{3 n+1}{2}-\frac{n}{2} a_{n} \text {. }
$$
(1) Write down the first three terms of the sequence $\left\{a_{n}\right\}$;
(2) Find the general term formula for the sequence $\left\{a_{n}\right\}$ (include the derivation process);
(3) Let $b_{n}=\frac{1}{a_{n}-1}\left(n \in \mathbf{N}_{+}\right)$, find the sum of the first $n$ terms of the sequence $\left\{b_{n}\right\}$.

Given the complex number $z=3+bi$ ($b\in\mathbb{R}$), and $(1+3i)\cdot z$ is a purely imaginary number.
(1) Find the complex number $z$ and its conjugate $\overline{z}$;
(2) If $\omega=\frac{z}{2+i}$, find the modulus of the complex number $|\omega|$.

In $\triangle ABC$, $\angle A = 60^{\circ}$, $c = \frac{3}{7} a$.

(I) Find the value of $\sin C$;

(II) If $a = 7$, find the area of $\triangle ABC$.

Among the following four propositions, the number of correct ones is (　　)  
① Any line in the coordinate plane has both an inclination angle and a gradient;  
② The range of values for a line's inclination angle is $[0, \pi]$;  
③ If a line has a gradient of $\tan(\alpha)$, then the inclination angle of this line is $\alpha$;  
④ If the inclination angle of a line is $\alpha$, then the gradient of this line is $\tan(\alpha)$.

A: 0  
B: 1  
C: 2  
D: 3

In an arithmetic sequence $\{a_n\}$, given $a_2 = 14$ and $a_5 = 5$.
(I) Find the general formula for $a_n$;
(II) Find the sum of the first 10 terms, $S_{10}$.

Example 5 (2002-2003 British Mathematical Olympiad) For each positive integer $n>1$, let $p(n)$ be the largest prime factor of $n$. Find all distinct positive integers $x, y, z$ that satisfy the following conditions.
(1) $x, y, z$ are in arithmetic progression;
(2) $p(x y z) \leqslant 3$.

Given the hyperbola equation $$\frac {x^{2}}{a^{2}}- \frac {y^{2}}{b^{2}}=1(a>0,b>0)$$, an ellipse C has its vertices at the foci of this hyperbola, and its foci at the vertices of the hyperbola.  
(1) When $$a= \sqrt {3}$$ and $b=1$, find the equation of ellipse C;  
(2) Under the condition of (1), the line $l: y=kx+ \frac {1}{2}$ intersects the y-axis at point P and intersects the ellipse at points A and B. If O is the origin, and the area ratio of $\triangle AOP$ to $\triangle BOP$ is 2:1, find the equation of line $l$;  
(3) If $a=1$, the ellipse C and the line $l': y=x+5$ have common points, find the minimum length of the major axis of this ellipse.
